python dump_tweets.py -h

Software   : dump_tweets.py
License    : GPLV3+
Author(s)  : Matteo Redaelli,  matteo DOT redaelli AT libero DOT it

USAGE: dump_tweets.py -q|--query string [-f|--file filename] [-i|--since_id number] [-v|--verbose] [-s|--slip number] [-d|--db dbhost:dbport:dbuser:dbpass:dbtable]

       -q string: string is the search string
       -d string: the tweets are saved to a MySQL db. strig is like 'dbhost:dbport:dbuser:dbpass:dbtable'
       -f string: max_id is saved to a file, it will be used for incremental dumping after a restart
       -s number: the script runs forever, it retrives tweets each number seconds

python dump_tweets.py -q pirelli  -d localhost:3306:tweets:twitter:twitter:tweets -f
